<br>
1 portal in all of Luclin? Come on, travels though 4-5 zones to get to the dungeon is not my idea of fun Verant.<br>
<br>
/rude Verant designers<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 8:01:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Luclin portals</span><hr size=1> What burns me is they made places like Katta Castellum unreachable for some.  Im a warrior, how am I supposed to reach that city?  I have no sow or invis so have to either run through Grimling and Tenebrous or through Grieg's End, the Scarlet Desert and the Twilight Sea and all those zones have mobs that could easily kill me in 1 or 2 hits.<br>
<br>
They seem to have made Luclin with 1 portal on purpose so that you can't go in specific zones until you are strong enough. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 8:17:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Luclin portals</span><hr size=1> Hrmm, I seem to recall doing a bit of reconnaisance for Banegrivm right when Luclin came out, and neither of us had SOW or invis.  We managed to make it through all right.  Now, if I could just remember how we did it.<br>
<br>
I do recall having to disarm traps once or twice, but it didn't save me from dying once. <p>Denoi<BR>
