<I>"Show me a good mouser and I'll show you a cat with bad breath" -- Garfield</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uartillis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 10:41:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Luclin portals</span><hr size=1> It does sound strange that luclin isn't litered with wizard portals.  The combine empire that first traveled to Luclin are the same ones who also created all of the wizard spires we see on norrath (from my understanding).  So if these enlightened combine empire people created the spires, why havn't they made any on luclin? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 238<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 10:50:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Luclin portals</span><hr size=1> They have 'click and go' portles.  Just like doors, you click on them and they teleport you to another zone.  Also, Luclin doesn't have and PC wizards or Druids.  So why would they build wizard portals or druid rings? <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>
Taruun of Shar Val<BR><BR>
Master Cook <BR>
Lousy Fletcher<BR>
Grandmaster Lech<BR>
<I>"Show me a good mouser and I'll show you a cat with bad breath" -- Garfield</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 7:12:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Luclin portals</span><hr size=1> Well there are some NPC wizards in Luclin, at least some sell spells to wizards only...<br>
<br>
The combine empire rules Norrath before Luclin and they created a lot of spires there. Why wouldn't they do the same on their new homeland ?<br>
<br>
So far my nexus gate has been pretty much useless: the zones are not that big in Luclin so gating to come back two zones instead of walking is a waste of mana. If only I could use it from Norrath but I can't, porting to the Nexus from there is a priviledge reserved to the Al'Krappor corporation <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Den <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uazdonsoulforger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azdon Soulforger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 7:18:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Luclin portals</span><hr size=1> Luclin is designed not to be an easy hunt, if you are fient of heart ovoid it, it is for the hardy adventurer only (mobs are crazy, go in expecting to die and relve in the times you don't, it's a game make it what you will <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 10:47:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Luclin portals</span><hr size=1> Luclin is pretty much a breeze to travel through. All the zones are so small. Verant did introduce some choke points (like Paludal Caverns) to try and keep kittens near their starting city and to keep Norrathian newbies from running all over the moon. But that seems very reasonable.<br>
<br>
Katta Castellum is very easy to get to with Invis (Nexus, Haven, Echo, Fungal, Twilight, Katta). Sure, that's a lot of zones, but they're all sooo small. It takes more time to zone from one to the next than it does to run through them.<br>
<br>
Without invis, Fungus Grove would be &quot;ugly&quot;, so you have to go up through Tenebrous (Nexus, Haven, Paludal, Hollowshade, Grimling, Tenebrous, Katta). This is a little longer, but easily do-able. Tenebrous is a dangerous place, but many things see invisible there anyway. Actually, for this path, Levitate is a very handy spell, if you have it.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm not sure why youngsters would need to get to Katta Castellum anyway. The only reason I can think of is to do the House of Midst quest to raise faction in Haven, but that's not really necessary. <p>Grimwyrd Storm<BR>
(Lux Aeternam)<BR>
30th Human Druid of Karana<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 12:33:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Luclin portals</span><hr size=1> New Bard spells are only sold on Katta, including the level 9 one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Luclin is not a good place to wander around if you don't know exactly where your going.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 11:49:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  bard song</span><hr size=1> Yeah, having a level 9 bard song available only in Katta is pretty poor planning IMO. It's really only a useful song for low levels too. (It makes your weapon hit magical. By the time you could travel &quot;safely&quot; to Katta to get it yourself, you probably will have obtained a magic weapon already anyway.) The quests in Katta and the zones around it are geared for much higher levels than 9.<br>
<br>
Then again, I guess you could consider it a rite of passage, sneaking all the way out there to get your song. Kind of like how non-DE enchanters used to have to infiltrate Neriak to get their enchant metal spells. I'm actually rather peeved that they're now available in Felwithe too; takes the fun out of it. The difference there, of course, is that the enchanter had the tools to infiltrate Neriak by himself (illusion, alliance, invis). The bard has nothing but a drum and a prayer that he can outrun anything that jumps him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 2:17:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: bard song</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I wasn't aware that there was a 9th level bard song only available in Katta. That bites.<br>
<br>
A Vah Shir bard could give it a try and probably be fine. Might die once or twice trying to get through Grimling Forest and Tenebrous Mountains, but at 9th level that's no big deal. Just go naked and run fast.<br>
<br>
However, Norrathian bards would need to get through Fungus Grove or Paludal Caverns and that's not really feasible at 9th without someone to help you with Invisibility/Camouflage. <p>Grimwyrd Storm<BR>
(Lux Aeternam)<BR>
30th Human Druid of Karana<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulorddenman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Denman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 2:30:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: bard song</span><hr size=1> Potential rationale for lack of teleport spires in Luclin.  The spires are made of materials found only in Norrath.  Luclin, being a satellite, doesn't have the same materials as Norrath.  Therefore, no spires in Luclin.<br>
<br>
This is probably an after the fact rationalization.  But just my 2 cp.<br>
<br>
Maedhros <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 3:07:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: bard song</span><hr size=1> According to Verant, the quadroliths pre-date the Combine Empire and no one knows how to build them. The quads in the Nexus (and the mysterious black sphere) would have theoretically been there prior to the moon's settlement by the Vah Shir and the three Combine Factions.<br>
<br>
The Vah Shir got &quot;transported&quot; up here in some sort of large natural or supernatural event (presumably due to the Kerran/Heretic war and/or the event that created the Hole). They were the first &quot;modern Norrathians&quot; to get to Luclin, but had no ability to make quadroliths (spires).<br>
<br>
The only reason the Combine Empire knew there was a quadrolith on Luclin is because some of their greatest minds &quot;sensed&quot; it there.<br>
<br>
The Loyalists, led by Imeratur Tsaph Katta, took one-way passage to Luclin to flee a coup attempt by Seru. Then split into the Shadow Haven group (who stayed near Nexus to investigate learning how to return to Norrath) and the Katta Castellum group (who ventured to Luclin's surface to restart the Combine Empire as they saw it). The Inquisition of Seru followed them later to the moon and founded Santus Seru.<br>
<br>
None of these three factions had the power to make quadroliths either. The House of Midst in Shadow Haven had been studying the means to return to Norrath for a long time, but it took Al'Kabor of Norrath to recently figure out how to open two-way travel between Norrath and Luclin.<br>
<br>
Anyway, my only point is that no one currently knows how to make quadroliths, and Luclin was settled after the time when the ancients built the quadroliths, so there is no reason why there should be more spires on Luclin.<br>
<br>
As a side note, the druids are attuned to Norrath and no druid rings are found on Luclin either <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
